I want you all to meet Tyler who was born with 2 extra nipples.  I performed a surgical removal of the extra nipples on my TV show Dr. 90210.  I truly enjoyed getting to know Tyler who is a pre-med student and had a true interest in surgery and science and I am so excited for her future. 

Extra nipples or supernumerary nipples occur in 1-6% of the population and many people don’t even realize they have them since they usually get mistaken for a mole or birthmark in the armpit or on the chest or abdomen.  The extra nipples sit along the milk line - as they do with other mammals.

The extra nipples range in size from being very small to actually having breast tissue under them and in the majority of cases they are benign but it still important to get them checked out by a doctor like any other pigmented lesion. Many patients like Tyler do choose to have them removed for comfort reasons because sometimes they catch or rub on clothing.  They can easily be excised under local anesthesia and usually only a a few sutures are needed. #plasticsurgery #dr90210 @surgeon

Dr. Cat Begovic is a board-certified plastic surgeon in Los Angeles and Beverly Hills, California. She graduated from Harvard University with Honors in Molecular and Cellular biology. Dr. Cat specializes in tummy tuck, labiaplasty, mommy makeover, liposuction, breast augmentation, BBL, revision plastic surgery, and other highly skilled plastic surgery procedures.

I wanted to share with you this stunning transformation of my patient @brookebarrows whose inspiring story was shared on Dr. 90210. Brooke lost over 200 pounds through diet and exercise - her tummy tuck to remove the excess remaining skin and tighten her abdominal wall was the finishing touch after all that hard work.  Her results are so natural, you can’t even tell she had surgery done. She is a successful plus sized model and models a lot of swimwear and two-piece outfits. When I performed this surgery - I took into consideration all the little details - keeping her scar thin and low and symmetric, creating my “signature natural looking belly button”, shaping her waist and abdomen to create the appearance of abs, and all the while keeping her curves.  Brooke - I feel so blessed to have you as my patient, thank you for being so inspiring, and I am so excited for all the amazing things your future holds. @surgeon

#dr90210 #plasticsurgeon #tummytuck

node.text:
I specialize in labiaplasty and vaginal rejuvenation.  For those of you who aren’t familiar with these terms, labiaplasty is a plastic surgery procedure that reduces and reshapes the labia minora.  Over 10 years ago I authored a book chapter on this topic, and then since then from doing hundreds of labiaplasties and studying the anatomy and aesthetics of this area, I have developed my very own surgical technique that creates a natural looking, tucked in, symmetric shape, little to no pain and an almost invisible scar. I often combine this with clitoral hood reduction in order to create an even and gentle curve that blends seamlessly.  

However what makes me a pioneer in vaginal cosmetic surgery is not just my surgical techniques, but more so that I have helped bring the topic of vaginal cosmetic surgery to the forefront of every day conversation.  Through my social media, you tube videos, and TV shows and media interviews on this topic, I have helped to make talking about vaginal cosmetic surgery not taboo.  Through educating the public on why women seek this surgery and creating a better understanding of what women can do to seek solutions for this area of the body, it has helped break the barrier of embarrassment related to this topic. Women who seek labiaplasty complain of discomfort because of rubbing or twisting of the labia, issues with hygiene, avoidance of leggings, swimwear or other tight fitting clothing, or because they feel self conscious during intimacy because of labial asymmetry or excess labial show and volume. It significantly improves the quality of life for women who seek this surgery. Im so proud of Jessi and I admire her courage for sharing her labiaplasty journey on Dr. 90210 #labiaplasty #thepussycatdolls

What is the difference between skin and fat?

My patient from Episode 3 of my show Dr. 90210 wanted to get her pre baby body back after pregnancy and thought she had a lot of abdominal fat after pregnancy but in fact it was mostly excess skin.

A tummy tuck repairs the abdominal muscles, tightens the abdominal wall and removes and tightens excess skin.  Liposuction removes and thins excess fat.

Ashley first had a tummy tuck and then liposuction of her back and waist with fat transfer to her butt.  She did not have liposuction to her abdomen.
You can see how the tummy tuck alone created a flat and contoured natural looking abdomen and using my special belly button technique she has a natural looking “innie” belly button with hidden scar.  Her tummy tuck incision is low and thin.  The liposuction with fat transfer accentuated the waist.  She has a beautiful result and I am so grateful to be her surgeon #dr90210 @surgeon #plasticsurgery #tummytuck

“Dr. Cat Begovic says her plastic surgery practice is “at least five times busier” than before “Dr. 90210” premiered amid the coronavirus pandemic.

The 43-year-old said her “mommy makeovers” — which include the midsection, body contouring, breast surgery and even vaginal cosmetic surgery — are in high demand.

“I think it’s more just because people are at home, they’re able to work from home, able to care for themselves a little better,” she told Page Six. “They had their caretaker with them usually, whereas normally they would have to block off a huge amount of time, make more arrangements in order to be able to recover from surgery. So I think that people being able to relax and rest and give themselves the time and care they need after surgery has made it definitely busier for plastic surgery in general.”

A lot of you have asked me if Breast Implant Illness is a real thing.  Yes, it is very real and is devastating to the women who develop it.  I personally have had three close friends who had it and I know how much they went through.  Luckily none of my patients have developed it but my friends’ experiences as well as the recent Allergan breast implant recall truly shook me. I am so thankful I never placed any of the recalled implants in someone - just the thought having a recalled product in your body is scary.
I stopped doing breast augmentation for a while, for two reasons - I wanted to find out more information on my own and also listen to the experiences of more women who have suffered from BII. I also don’t want to glorify breast implants while so many women are suffering and not being heard. That’s the reason why I didn’t do any breast augmentation surgeries or breast implants on my TV show Dr. 90210.
I discuss all the potential risks with my patients, long term effects, and also let them know that there is a lot we don’t know about implants and there is an ongoing research. The FDA recently came out with new black box warnings for breast implants and I make sure that every patient is educated and aware of possible side effects. I also send everyone to platforms and pages such as @breast_implant_illness where women share their stories and experiences with breast implants illness as well as where to get help. These groups have done a lot for women to educate themselves and advocate for themselves.
I know this is a very uncomfortable discussion but that’s why we need to talk about it. It’s important for women to get as much information as possible so they can make the best possible choices for themselves. It’s important for all women to be heard and to never dismiss what they have to say and their experience. That’s why I’m making this post to make it possible for women to be heard on my page, both women who have experienced BII but also women who have positive experiences with breast augmentation. Open and honest communication is the best way for us to care for ourselves and each other.  Please share your story in comments below. #bii #breastimplantillness

I’m proud to say that I’m one of the pioneers in the field of Labiaplasty and that I’ve developed my very own special, surgical technique that has no pain, a nearly invisible scar, and creates a natural looking, symmetric and tucked in shape. Through the advocacy I have done to normalize discussions about Labiaplasty and have women feel more comfortable to seek solutions for themselves, Labiaplasty is becoming more popular. It is one of the surgeries I specialize and one of the surgeries I perform the most. In most cases the procedure is more than cosmetic, it truly improves a woman’s quality of life.

In your consultation, myself and my staff will do everything we can to make you as comfortable as possible. I will discuss what your specific concerns are and develop a customized surgical plan for you.

Over 30% of of my medical practice are patients that fly in from out of town or overseas for surgery. We have  simple process for our out of town patients and would start with a video consult with photos. You can go to the Out of Town patient link on my website or click on the highlight stories for more information. 

To see before and after images please visit beautybydrcat.com (link in bio)

I know many of you are new followers, so I wanted to re-introduce myself on my instagram and tell you a little bit about myself. My name is Dr. Cat Begovic, I’m a mother, wife, a board certified plastic surgeon and a founder of the luxurious skincare brand MD GLAM. I’m also a cast member of the TV show Dr. 90210 on E! 

I grew up in Delaware, lived in Boston throughout my Harvard college days and finally Los Angeles got my heart. I moved here full of dreams & ambition and absolutely loved it from the very start.  With my first exposure to surgery when volunteering at the local hospital in high school and stepping into the OR, I knew that surgery was my calling and I could do nothing else. From an early age I have been a rebellious unapologetic nonconformist with my own individual style and expression that I balanced out with my academic record which included a perfect SAT score, being a Presidential Scholar, and graduating with honors in Molecular & Cellular biology from Harvard.  Someone once said that well behaved girls rarely changed the world. I believe in challenging stereotypes so all girls can feel free to be themselves and know that with dedication and hard work anything is possible.

At UCLA, I took a special interest in stem cell research as well as the science of skin care, publishing many research papers in plastic surgery and scientific journals on these topics.

I perform a range of invasive and non-invasive plastic surgery procedures that include Labiaplasty, Tummy tuck, Mommy Makeovers, Liposuction, and Brazilian Butt Lift. My patients range from moms who are on their journey of self-discovery, to celebrities, actresses, sports stars, to ordinary people who just need some uplifting in life. Regardless who enters my practice, everyone gets celebrity treatment. My goal for every patient is to give them an unparalleled, incredible patient experience and meticulous and amazing aesthetic results.

I’d love to hear from all of you as well in the comments below and if you have any questions let me know. Love, Dr. Cat @surgeon @mymdglam 

#thisismystory #mystory #dreamscometrue

node.text:
Being named one of Maxim’s 2021 Hot 100 was impactful for me in so many ways.  Maxim magazine made the following statement, “While the list has previously consisted almost entirely of models, the balance of pulchritudinous power has shifted. While physical beauty is still an important part of the equation, our attraction algorithm takes many more factors into account...Change is a good thing, we think you’ll agree.”

I cannot agree more. I believe that the groundbreaking and bold move by Maxim is the spark that will change the world. I consider it the first step in redefining beauty for women - where the world can expand its perceptions of beauty and value women as a whole person, the inside and out.

Breaking women free from societal stereotypes is what I have been doing my entire life. Women should be able to express their personal style and be seen for who they are, their talents, and what they are capable of achieving and not be limited by their appearance.  I am unapologetic in celebrating my femininity in the male dominated field of plastic surgery thriving in a career that I love. Women should be able to pursue their passions and dreams free from judgment or preconceived notions of what they are supposed to look like. There are no limits.  Whatever you believe you can achieve.  I hope that this helps women of all ages to believe and empower themselves and find freedom from the traditional constraints of society. 

#maximtop100 #maximmagazine #plasticsurgeon #womeninspiringwomen @maximmag

Here are some recent examples of my Quick Recovery Natural Tummy Tuck Surgery.  All of these after photos are just 1 week after surgery.  You can see that my patients have no bruising, and although they are still slightly bent over, at 1 week they are walking around with no pain.

I have developed a gentle tummy technique that has a quick recovery and little to no pain.  My patients need no prescription pain medication, at most a few Tylenol, and they are walking a few hours after surgery.  It’s hard for many to believe but it is true. I believe it is important to be gentle when taking care of patients and to perform surgery meticulously to avoid creating pain.  Many patients who desire tummy tucks don’t end up doing it because of the horrible pain they have read about on the internet or from friends who had it done elsewhere.  With everything I do, I do it with care and treat my patients when they are under anesthesia as I would my family or my closest friends.  In my IG stories I regularly show my tummy tucks 1 day, 1 week, up to a year after surgery to help you all visualize how the recovery can be a pain-free and easy experience. I would hate for anyone not to have a life changing surgery because they feel that the recovery is going to be horrible - it doesn’t have to be.  For my patients out there reading this, if you feel comfortable sharing your experience - it may help others who may be considering surgery. 

For more before and after photos go to my website beautybydrcat.com  #plasticsurgery #tummytuck #tummytuckrecovery #dr90210 @surgeon.
